# Python Development

Handle Python development tasks following the project's Python style guide and best practices.

Refer to the following files for guidance:
- Python style guide: @.agent-os/standards/code-style/python-style.md
- General code style: @.agent-os/standards/code-style.md
- Best practices: @.agent-os/standards/best-practices.md
- Tech stack: @.agent-os/product/tech-stack.md

## Key Guidelines
- Use Python 3.12+ features and async-first architecture
- Follow PEP 8 with project-specific overrides (4 spaces, 88 char line length)
- Use type hints throughout the codebase
- Implement proper error handling with custom exceptions
- Use Pydantic for data validation and configuration
- Write comprehensive tests with pytest
- Use structured logging with structlog
- Follow the project's established patterns and architecture
